name: B-1B Lancer™
description: Is a supersonic variable-sweep wing, heavy bomber used by the United States Air Force and is commonly referred to as the bone due to its “B-1” designation.  It is one of three strategic bombers in the U.S. Air Force fleet as of 2018.  The other two are the B-2 Spirit "Stealth Bomber"™ and the B-52 Stratofortress™
